2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the uplink pilot training sequence and downlink power allocation, which are important aspects of wireless networking and communication. 

3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper may be relevant to social networks that rely on wireless communication, such as mobile social networks. 

4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper may be relevant to multimedia applications that require high-capacity wireless communication, such as video streaming. 

5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): The paper may be relevant to the societal impact of wireless communication technologies, such as their role in bridging the digital divide.
